    <h1>Complexity</h1>
    <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mb-6">Maheshwari &amp; Smid &middot; Ch. 8 &middot; <a href="https://cglab.ca/~michiel/TheoryOfComputation/">Introduction to Theory of Computation</a></p>

    <div class="bg-zinc-800 rounded-lg p-5 mb-8 callout">
      <p class="text-lg" style="max-width:none"><strong>P</strong> is the class of problems solvable in polynomial time. <strong>NP</strong> is the class whose solutions can be <em>verified</em> in polynomial time. Whether P = NP is the central open question. The <strong>Cook-Levin theorem</strong> proves that SAT is NP-complete: every NP problem reduces to it in polynomial time.</p>
    </div>

